-yLPL1d11icq0F.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*Yt-yLPL1d11icq0F.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*Yt-yLPL1d11icq0F.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:558/0*Yt-yLPL1d11icq0F.jpeg 558w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:279/0*Yt-yLPL1d11icq0F.jpeg"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">Logistic Regression</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Advantages of Linear Regression :</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It makes <strong>no assumptions about distributions of classes</strong> in feature space.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Easily extended to multiple classes</strong> (multinomial regression).</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Natural probabilistic view of class predictions.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Quick to train and very fast at classifying unknown records.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Good accuracy for many simple data sets.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Resistant to overfitting.</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Disadvantages of Logistic Regression :</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It <strong>cannot handle continuous variables</strong>.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">If independent variables are not correlated with the target variable, then Logistic regression does not work.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Requires large sample size</strong> for stable results.</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5"><strong>2. Support Vector Machines (SVM)</strong></h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Support vector machines (SVMs) are a set of supervised learning methods used for classification, regression and outlier detection.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
