            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/0*167DP-0bMK0mQZY8.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">Support Vector Machines (SVMs)</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Advantages of SVMs include:</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">They maximize the margin of decision boundary</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">They can handle large feature spaces.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">SVMs work well with semi-structured and unstructured data.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">They can use the concept of kernel trick to solve any complex problem.</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Disadvantages of SVMs include:</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">SVMs can be difficult to implement when the number of classes is more than 2.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">SVMs take a long time for training and they are sensitive to noise.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Choosing a good kernel function is not easy in SVM and requires a lot of testing.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Hyperparameters like gamma and cost-C are not easy to fine-tune.</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5"><strong>3. K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)</strong></h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">K- Nearest Neighbors is a Supervised machine learning algorithm which can be used for classification as well as regression. It does not make an assumption about the underlying data distribution pattern.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The classification of objects in KNN is made on the basis of plurality of vote of its closest K neighbors, where K can be any small positive integer. The algorithm eagerly learns during the training step. It can predict whether a new point will fall into a given cluster.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:57%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 429px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:858/format:webp/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 858w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 429px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:858/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png 858w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:429/0*MBk1znDEmccTa8jO.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">Steps to apply KNN Algorithms</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Steps to apply K-Nearest Neighbors Algorithms:</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Select a value for K (odd number)</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Choose a sample data point that needs to be classified and compute distance to its n training samples.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Sort the distances and take K closest samples.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Assign the sample data point to the class that has the majority vote of its K neighbors.</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7"><strong>Cons of KNN Algorithms:</strong></h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">KNN is computationally expensive as it searches the nearest neighbors for the new point at the prediction stage. Memory requirement for KNN is high. Sensitive to outliers, accuracy is impacted by noise or irrelevant data.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5"><strong>4. XGBoost (eXtreme Gradient Boosting)</strong></h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Extreme Gradient Boosting (XGBoost) is an open-source library that provides an efficient and effective implementation of the gradient boosting algorithm.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Gradient boosting belongs to ensemble machine learning algorithms that can be used for classification or regression predictive modeling problems.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In an Ensemble method the algorithm <strong>combines the predictions from multiple machine learning algorithms</strong> together to make more accurate predictions than any individual model.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Some of the reasons why XGBoost is used:</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It is a powerful algorithm with high speed and performance.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Processing power of modern multicore computers can be utilized by the XGBoost algorithm.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It is cost-effective to train on large datasets.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Consistently outperform all single algorithm methods.</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5"><strong>5. AdaBoost (Adaptive Boosting)</strong></h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">AdaBoost is a <strong>Boosting Algorithm</strong> which includes a <strong>group of algorithms that utilize weighted averages to make weak learners into strong learners</strong>. Each model that runs decides what features the next model will focus on.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The performance of decision trees on binary classification problems is frequently boosted using the AdaBoost algorithm. <strong>It is done by building a model from the training data, then creating a second model that attempts to correct the errors from the first model.</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">AdaBoost keeps on adding the models until the training set starts getting predicted perfectly or a given number of models is added. It is <strong>less susceptible to over-fitting</strong> than other learning algorithms.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:83%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 609px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1218/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 1218w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 609px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1218/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw 1218w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:609/0*IsjYapnhdD0gsmIw"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">AdaBoost (Adaptive Boosting)</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5"><strong>6. Artificial Neural Network ( ANN )</strong></h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">ANNs are <strong>composed of multiple nodes</strong>, which imitate biological neurons of the human brain. The <strong>node </strong>is connected via <strong>links </strong>and they can interact with each other.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Each node takes input data and performs simple operations on that data</strong>. The results are passed on to other nodes. The output from each node is called its <strong>activation</strong>. Each connection from a node has a weight associated with it. ANNs learn by altering weight values each time.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
